I"	<p>The TYPE command is use to set the <em>personality</em> of a sensor. In the <a href="rf_modes.html">Modes of Operation</a> section we described the two modes of an RF module. You use the TYPE command to configure which <em>mode</em> you want the module be in. Here is a list of all the types available:</p>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Type Number</th>
      <th>Description</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>1</td>
      <td>Thermistor Temperature Sensor</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>2</td>
      <td>Gateway</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>3</td>
      <td>DHT22 Humidity Sensor</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>4</td>
      <td>DS18B20 Temperature Sensor</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>5</td>
      <td>Analog A</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>6</td>
      <td>Analog B</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>7</td>
      <td>Relay</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>8</td>
      <td>SHT21 Humidity and Temperature Sensor</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>9</td>
      <td>BME280 Pressure, Humidity and Temperature Sensor</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>10</td>
      <td>HTU21 Humidity and Temperature Sensor</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p><strong>Type 2</strong> is <em>Gateway Mode</em> which enables the serial port so that the RF module can interface with a micro-controller (e.g. Raspberry Pi, PC, Arduino etcâ€¦).</p>

<p><strong>All other types</strong> are <em>Sensor Mode</em>. The <em>Sensor Mode</em> types define what sensor is attached to the RF module (e.g. a type 4 sensor is DS18B20 temperature sensor). The sensor type is required in order to enter <a href="sleep_modes.html">timed sleep cycle</a>.</p>

<p><strong>Command:</strong> TYPE[<em>p1</em>] <br />
<strong>Response:</strong> TYPE[<em>p1</em>]</p>

<p><em>Where</em>: p1 = Type Number from the above table</p>

<p>Example:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>python rf_config.py 03 TYPE1
SENT     : 03TYPE1
RECEIVED : 03TYPE1----
</code></pre></div></div>
